description:
Published by the UK wing of Panini Comics. 
 
Marvel Heroes Reborn was the fourth Panini Comics Marvel Collector's Edition released in 1997. Originally it reprinted Iron Man Vol 2 and Fantastic Four Vol 2. With issue 17 it added the Hulk to become the same size as the other Collector's Editions. With issue 19 It began to reprint Iron Man Vol 3 and Fantastic Four Vol 3. In issue 39 the Hulk was replaced with the Avengers Vol 3. The comic was cancelled with issue 42 in 2000, due to poor sales. It was eventually replaced with Avengers United
name: Marvel Heroes Reborn

description:
This is the second volume of the Swamp Thing.

Notes:

  • Based on the indicia the title of this series is "The Saga of the Swamp Thing" (issues #1-38, 42-45) although the indicia only reads "Swamp Thing" for issues #39-41. This gets even more confusing with the cover title that first reads "The SAGA of the Swamp Thing" (issues #1-30) before switching to "Swamp Thing" (issues #31-45), too.
  • Winner of an Eagle Award for "Favorite Writer" (Alan Moore) and "Favorite Comic Book" in 1984.

The numbering is then continued in Swamp Thing #46.

Annuals

  • The Saga of Swamp Thing Annual #1: Has no ties to the series, comic adaptation of the film released the same year this series was launched.
  • Swamp Thing Annual #2: Directly tied into the series during Alan Moore's run and concludes the story "Love and Death", the annual takes place after #31.

Collected Editions:

  • Saga of the Swamp Thing (#21-27)
  • Love and Death (#28-34)
  • The Curse (#35-42)
  • A Murder of Crows (#43-45, Vol. 2: #46-50)
name: The Saga of Swamp Thing
